    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201013/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-10-13"><time>2020-10-13</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>LON­DON • Sal­ford City co-owner Paul Sc­holes has been ap­pointed care­taker man­ager fol­low­ing the sack­ing of Gra­ham Alexan­der, the English League Two club said yes­ter­day.</p>
    <p>The for­mer Manch­ester United mid­fielder last coached Old­ham in League Two but left in March last year af­ter only 31 days, cit­ing board in­ter­fer­ence.</p>
    <p>Sal­ford, who se­cured their first pro­mo­tion to the fourth tier via the play-offs last sea­son, are co-owned by United’s Class of ’92, in­clud­ing greats like David Beck­ham, Ryan Giggs, Nicky Butt and Gary and Phil Neville, with Sin­ga­porean bil­lion­aire Peter Lim hold­ing the other 40 per cent.</p>


